    </section>

    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl">Building partnerships and capabilities</h2>
      <div class="text-base leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-4">
        <p>As the design system and the team matured, we started to pursue active partnerships with other teams to embed systems thinking into feature work. This was done with the intent of driving scalability and velocity beyond the foundational design system elements. Two example of this were:</p>
        {% call ul() %}
          {% call li() %}Partnering with the team focused on GoodRx's new condition subscription offerings. This collaboration involved updating design system elements to meet their needs and helping them build more complex reusable components to power key facets of their experience, like their intake flows and subscriber dashboard experience.{% endcall %}
          {% call li() %}Partnering with the Payments team to standardize payment and address entry and selection experiences. This involved auditing existing implementations and then building standard components to consolidate the current solutions. The team then also lead to work to update the account-level payment method and address management experiences, enabling key capabilities across all teams.{% endcall %}
        {% endcall %}
      </div>

      {% call grid2(classes="mt-8", maxWidth="1200px") %}
        {{ gridImage("/images/payment-components.png", "", "A sample of the payment components and related documentation.") }}
        {{ gridImage("/images/address-components.png", "", "A sample of the address components and related documentation.") }}
      {% endcall %}

    </section>

    <section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <h2 class="text-xl">Impact</h2>
      <div class="text-base leading-relaxed flex flex-col gap-4">
        <p>Through our ongoing efforts to ensure the design system, and the experience of working with it, are optimal, we’ve achieved meaningful results:</p>
        {% call ul() %}
          {% call li() %}Across Web, iOS, and Android, all launches by all teams utilize design system elements as the foundation of their UI. Precise coverage numbers vary on whether a launch involves introducing new UI/UX paradigms, or works exclusively with existing pieces.{% endcall %}
          {% call li() %}We build proactive partnerships with teams around the organization to add to or update the design system to support emerging needs, in advance of the actual feature work beginning.{% endcall %}
          {% call li() %}We’re meaningfully embedded in team critiques, providing systems guidance when appropriate. The team’s input is sought out in strategic and tactical conversations to help inform how problems are solved.{% endcall %}
        {% endcall %}
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</div>
